    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "But is this much different from e.g. contracts that allow use of arbitrary ERC20 tokens? Users of the contract are aware that this is the case, and the contract may have specific logic to defend against poorly / maliciously formed tokens.\r\n\r\nSimilarly here, users of the contract would be aware that the library can be altered. Whether there are sufficient safeguards in place is up to the contract, e.g. only allowing switching to pre-defined addresses (which also have verifiable code).",
