    "created_at": "2017-08-08T12:29:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-08-08T12:29:25Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I guess an easy syntactical way would be to allow an address at the place the library is used (if it is missing, it can still be supplied compile time):\r\n```\r\nfunction f() {\r\n  L(0x1234).f();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nhowever that would be repetitive so there must be a way to configure libraries.\r\n\r\nHow about \r\n\r\n```\r\nusing L at 0x1234;\r\nfunction f() {\r\n  L.f();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs a second step it could be extended to not only support hexadecimal literals, but variables:\r\n\r\n```\r\nuint libraryAddress;\r\n\r\nfunction setLibrary(address _address) owner only {\r\n  libraryAddress = _address;\r\n}\r\n\r\nusing L at libraryAddress;\r\n\r\nfunction f() {\r\n  L.f();\r\n}\r\n\r\n```",
